## Non-negotiable rules
1. UI language is Swedish. NEVER hardcode Swedish strings in components — add them to `src/locales/sv.ts` and access via `useTranslation()`.
2. There are TWO `updateLead` functions. Always import from `src/lib/leads.ts` (logs activity). Never from `src/lib/database.ts` (no logging).
3. Invoice templates use `settings.template_type = 'invoice'`. Quote templates use `'quote'`. The TemplateBuilder saves `design_options` inside `settings.design_options`, not at the top level — always read both: `template?.design_options || template?.settings?.design_options || {}`.
4. Lead lifecycle: new → qualified (quote created) → won (order created or quote accepted). Marking a lead as won uses fire-and-forget: `updateLead(id, { status: 'won' }).catch(...)`.
5. TypeScript must stay clean. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after any changes to verify.

## Key files to know
- `src/lib/quoteTemplates.ts` — QuoteTemplate type, default templates, CRUD helpers
- `src/components/InvoicePreview.tsx` — template-driven invoice renderer; static sections wrapped in `{!template && (...)}`
- `src/components/invoices/modals/InvoiceDetailsModal.tsx` — template picker UI
